Sports Minister Sunday Dare has congratulated the Nigerian national women basketball team, D’Tigress for picking a ticket to the FIBA Women World Cup. The ladies, who are three times Afrobasketball champions beat their Malian opponents 73-69 yesterday to qualify as Africa’s sole representatives. They had earlier beaten the highly rated, world number five, France 67-65, after losing their opening game to China. Dare praised the queens of the court for doing the nation proud and showing dogged determination in all their games.   Napoli 1-1 Inter : Italian legend faults Osimhen ‘s rating     NTDs: Troost-Ekong to captain Team Thrive Africa     Eguavoen, Amuneke ‘ll deliver Qatar 2022 ticket, says…   The FIBA Women Basketball World Cup will take place on Sydney, Australia in September. - Advertisement - In a related development, the National President of Authentic Nigeria Football and Allied Sports Supporters Club, Prince Abayomi Ogunjimi has also congratulated D’Tigress for a job well down. Abayomi in a release, described the team as a true ambassadors of Nigeria , having won two games against France and Mali to qualify. He said: ” Authentic Nigeria Football and Allied Sports Supporters Club heartily congratulates the Nigeria’s D’Tigress for exhibiting the true Nigerian spirit and cementing a qualification for FIBA women World Cup in Australia, the game against France showed a great fighting spirit, our girls are true Ambassadors, wining Mali today (Sunday) has shown that Nigerians are winners. “ On behalf of members of ANFASSC , we say a big congratulations and wish you all success in the next games .” SPONSORED